Let's point out that *.UUCP should NOT map into a silent forwarding to
uunet.uu.net, which is not advertised as providing such a service.  In
providing this ``service'' to your local users, you are exploiting a
grace that uunet.uu.net and its subscribers are currently providing.  If
the burden of providing this grace to the community becomes too high, as
it is always in danger of doing, uunet.uu.net will stop providing it,
and you and everybody will suffer.

You basically need to know more about uucp routing than simply sending
everything to uunet.uu.net.

Route things to different pseudo-nets with your sendmail.cf, not with
your domain system.  There are enough lies circulating in the
distributed domain database without anybody intentionally adding more.

		Craig

